n feel amid a host of sights, sounds and tastes to savour Plan your next getaway with Travel Time, featuring travel deals, destinations and gear.\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travel_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999671680294485, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travel Time\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travel_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travel_Time\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a host\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1151}, {\"ngram\": \"sights\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1161}, {\"ngram\": \"your next getaway\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"travel deals\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"destinations\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"gear\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By signing up you consent to receive the above newsletter from Postmedia Network Inc. A welcome email is on its way.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmedia_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Postmedia Network Inc.\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmedia_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postmedia_Network\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the above newsletter\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"A welcome email\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"its way\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you do not see it, please check your junk folder.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your junk folder\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next issue of Travel Time will soon be in your inbox.\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1471, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travel_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999671680294485, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travel Time\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travel_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travel_Time\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The next issue\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We encountered an issue signing you up.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an issue\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please try again Interested in more newsletters?Browse here.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more newsletters?Browse\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some days it's easy to imagine you are the only tourist in town, an experience those impatient crowds lining up to enter The Louvre will not be privy to.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1740, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9999999888968888, \"rank\": 1.1102879272027504e-08, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only tourist\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1670}, {\"ngram\": \"town\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"an experience\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"those impatient crowds\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First and foremost, this is a city that worships food and with good reason.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"good reason\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The best chefs are celebrated like Hollywood movie stars; witness the large mural of culinary genius and local boy made good Paul Bocuse adorning a wall across from the magnificent food hall bearing his name.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 2054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1881, \"end\": 1890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.96493979196264e-16, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1971, \"end\": 1982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Bocuse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Bocuse\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Bocuse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Bocuse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The best chefs\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"the large mural\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1927}, {\"ngram\": \"culinary genius\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1946}, {\"ngram\": \"local boy\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"a wall\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"the magnificent food hall\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2036}, {\"ngram\": \"his name\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(A biennial world chef tournament is also named for him.)\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2112, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A biennial world chef tournament\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, Lyon's culinary fame has its roots in more modest circumstances, showing when the world serves you lemons it's possible to make more than just lemonade.\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its roots\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2153}, {\"ngram\": \"more modest circumstances\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2182}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"you lemons\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many working-class women here were employed as cooks by the aristocratic families of the city, but after France went through the horrors of the First World War, the political, social and financial worlds changed: the upshot was that these women were dismissed from their posts.\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999995970938, \"rank\": 2.3910655377837446e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many working-class women\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"cooks\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"the aristocratic families\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"the horrors\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"the First World War\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2432}, {\"ngram\": \"the political, social and financial worlds\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2476}, {\"ngram\": \"the upshot\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"these women\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"their posts\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having few other skills, they turned to what they knew best - cooking.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2622, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"few other skills\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They began offering popular dishes to the regular people of Lyon, using fresh, local ingredients.\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2683, \"end\": 2687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"popular dishes\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"the regular people\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2679}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh, local ingredients\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Soon their fame spread and the specialty meals they prepared from scratch eventually became famous beyond city boundaries.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their fame\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2736}, {\"ngram\": \"the specialty meals\", \"from\": 2748, \"to\": 2767}, {\"ngram\": \"scratch\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2794}, {\"ngram\": \"city boundaries\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2842}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today they are known collectively as Les Meres Lyonnaises - the Lyon mothers - and their cuisine still serves as the bedrock of a global reputation for fine dining.\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2908, \"end\": 2912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Les Meres\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2890}, {\"ngram\": \"their cuisine\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2940}, {\"ngram\": \"the bedrock\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 2968}, {\"ngram\": \"a global reputation\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"fine dining\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where best to taste such food?\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3040, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such food\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, with more than 4,000 restaurants, choice is on the menu.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 4,000 restaurants\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3079}, {\"ngram\": \"choice\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3087}, {\"ngram\": \"the menu\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, do as the locals do.\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3128, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the locals\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3124}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first port of call should be a bouchon establishment serving traditional fare.\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3211, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first port\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"call\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"a bouchon establishment\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"traditional fare\", \"from\": 3194, \"to\": 3210}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Fines Gueules, under the eyes and hands of chef Joel Salzi in the city's old quarter, is as good as it gets.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Fines Gueules\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3229}, {\"ngram\": \"the eyes\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3245}, {\"ngram\": \"hands\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3255}, {\"ngram\": \"chef Joel Salzi\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3274}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's old quarter\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mix with the locals, who can turn lunch into an all-afternoon affair with little coaxing, and try everything from Burgundy snails to homemade oxtail beef terrine and beef tripe.\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3440, \"end\": 3448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgundy\", \"score\": 0.9999999931078491, \"rank\": 6.8921147201172235e-09, \"text\": \"Burgundy\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgundy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgundy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the locals\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3345}, {\"ngram\": \"lunch\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3365}, {\"ngram\": \"an all-afternoon affair\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3394}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3434}, {\"ngram\": \"oxtail beef terrine\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3487}, {\"ngram\": \"beef tripe\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3502}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And why not live a little and immerse yourself in true Lyonnais culture with a sampling of the breaded pig's trotter?\", \"from\": 3504, \"to\": 3621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"true Lyonnais culture\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"a sampling\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3591}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaded pig's trotter\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3620}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After such a lunch it is hardly surprising that supper can only be appreciated after a good six-hour interlude.\", \"from\": 3623, \"to\": 3734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such a lunch\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3641}, {\"ngram\": \"that supper\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3677}, {\"ngram\": \"a good six-hour interlude\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3733}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Work up an appetite by visiting some of the wonderful Gallo-Roman ruins dotting the city; the two ancient open-air theatres are particularly striking, giving a glimpse into the importance the Romans placed on Lyon as part of their empire.\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3927, \"end\": 3933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999319009744757, \"rank\": 6.80996226267244e-05, \"text\": \"Romans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an appetite\", \"from\": 3743, \"to\": 3754}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3823}, {\"ngram\": \"the two ancient open-air theatres\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3858}, {\"ngram\": \"a glimpse\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3902}, {\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 3908, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 3956}, {\"ngram\": \"their empire\", \"from\": 3960, \"to\": 3972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the summer, they come alive once more, hosting concerts, theatre and dance evenings.\", \"from\": 3974, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 3981, \"to\": 3991}, {\"ngram\": \"hosting concerts\", \"from\": 4020, \"to\": 4036}, {\"ngram\": \"theatre and dance evenings\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nearby is the imposing Notre-Dame Basilica which offers breathtaking views of the city below.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the imposing Notre-Dame Basilica\", \"from\": 4077, \"to\": 4109}, {\"ngram\": \"breathtaking views\", \"from\": 4123, \"to\": 4141}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1870, Lyon's bishop pledged to erect a suitable monument to the Virgin Mary if the invading Prussians spared it.\", \"from\": 4161, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4170, \"end\": 4174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}, {\"begin\": 4228, \"end\": 4239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.8910608668601592, \"rank\": 0.12225779090028496, \"text\": \"Virgin Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 4256, \"end\": 4265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franco-Prussian_War\", \"score\": 0.9999981444306222, \"rank\": 1.7756953697434034e-06, \"text\": \"Prussians\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franco-Prussian_War\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franco-Prussian_War\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a suitable monument\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They did and he followed through - with more than a little help from 2,000 builders and artisans.\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4374, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than a little help\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4340}, {\"ngram\": \"2,000 builders\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4360}, {\"ngram\": \"artisans\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Down the hill - you can take the handy funicular - is the St. John Cathedral, resplendent in the old city square, especially in the evening when major buildings are illuminated.\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the hill\", \"from\": 4381, \"to\": 4389}, {\"ngram\": \"the handy funicular\", \"from\": 4405, \"to\": 4424}, {\"ngram\": \"the St. John Cathedral\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4452}, {\"ngram\": \"the old city square\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4488}, {\"ngram\": \"the evening\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4515}, {\"ngram\": \"major buildings\", \"from\": 4521, \"to\": 4536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With its strategic location between two great rivers, Lyon wasn't just a draw for the Romans.\", \"from\": 4555, \"to\": 4648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4609, \"end\": 4613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}, {\"begin\": 4641, \"end\": 4647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.9999319009744757, \"rank\": 6.80996226267244e-05, \"text\": \"Romans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its strategic location\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4582}, {\"ngram\": \"two great rivers\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4607}, {\"ngram\": \"just a draw\", \"from\": 4621, \"to\": 4632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Centuries afterwards, it became an important commercial hub and from that mercantile history sprung the silk trade, eventually making Lyon a global centre for weaving.\", \"from\": 4649, \"to\": 4816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4783, \"end\": 4787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an important commercial hub\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4708}, {\"ngram\": \"that mercantile history\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4741}, {\"ngram\": \"the silk trade\", \"from\": 4749, \"to\": 4763}, {\"ngram\": \"weaving\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although that dominance has waned, Lyon still enjoys a reputation for elaborate silk artistry in specialized shops.\", \"from\": 4818, \"to\": 4933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4853, \"end\": 4857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that dominance\", \"from\": 4827, \"to\": 4841}, {\"ngram\": \"a reputation\", \"from\": 4871, \"to\": 4883}, {\"ngram\": \"elaborate silk artistry\", \"from\": 4888, \"to\": 4911}, {\"ngram\": \"specialized shops\", \"from\": 4915, \"to\": 4932}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also houses several museums paying homage to the trade, including the Brochier Museum; a working enterprise that showcases 130 years and four generations of a family that first began fine silk work in 1890.\", \"from\": 4934, \"to\": 5143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5007, \"end\": 5015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brochier\", \"score\": 0.9999999991305231, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brochier\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brochier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brochier\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several museums\", \"from\": 4949, \"to\": 4964}, {\"ngram\": \"homage\", \"from\": 4972, \"to\": 4978}, {\"ngram\": \"the trade\", \"from\": 4982, \"to\": 4991}, {\"ngram\": \"a working enterprise\", \"from\": 5024, \"to\": 5044}, {\"ngram\": \"130 years\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5069}, {\"ngram\": \"four generations\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5090}, {\"ngram\": \"a family\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5102}, {\"ngram\": \"fine silk work\", \"from\": 5120, \"to\": 5134}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such family businesses are the city's entrepreneurial heartbeat - places such as the Galerie Saint Hubert, where owner Hubert Kilardjian still greets customers with the grace and charm he first displayed in opening the art gallery half a century ago, and the Chai St Olive, where two brothers bring freshly pressed grape juice from nearby vineyards and carry out all the processes of vinification in the heart of the city to create unique wines.\", \"from\": 5145, \"to\": 5590, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such family businesses\", \"from\": 5145, \"to\": 5167}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's entrepreneurial heartbeat - places\", \"from\": 5172, \"to\": 5217}, {\"ngram\": \"the Galerie Saint Hubert\", \"from\": 5226, \"to\": 5250}, {\"ngram\": \"owner Hubert Kilardjian\", \"from\": 5258, \"to\": 5281}, {\"ngram\": \"customers\", \"from\": 5295, \"to\": 5304}, {\"ngram\": \"the grace\", \"from\": 5310, \"to\": 5319}, {\"ngram\": \"the art gallery\", \"from\": 5360, \"to\": 5375}, {\"ngram\": \"the Chai St Olive\", \"from\": 5400, \"to\": 5417}, {\"ngram\": \"two brothers\", \"from\": 5425, \"to\": 5437}, {\"ngram\": \"freshly pressed grape juice\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5471}, {\"ngram\": \"nearby vineyards\", \"from\": 5477, \"to\": 5493}, {\"ngram\": \"all the processes\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5525}, {\"ngram\": \"vinification\", \"from\": 5529, \"to\": 5541}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 5545, \"to\": 5554}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5558, \"to\": 5566}, {\"ngram\": \"unique wines\", \"from\": 5577, \"to\": 5589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyon is easy to navigate with an excellent public transit system.\", \"from\": 5592, \"to\": 5657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5592, \"end\": 5596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an excellent public transit system\", \"from\": 5622, \"to\": 5656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For our stay, we chose the four-star Grand Hotel des Terreaux, a stately hotel, recently renovated and situated in the heart of the city.\", \"from\": 5658, \"to\": 5795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5695, \"end\": 5706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Brighton_Hotel\", \"score\": 0.9999990332066898, \"rank\": 9.667944921204764e-07, \"text\": \"Grand Hotel\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q27686\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Brighton_Hotel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Brighton_Hotel\"}, {\"begin\": 5711, \"end\": 5719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_des_Terreaux\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Terreaux\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_des_Terreaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_des_Terreaux\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our stay\", \"from\": 5662, \"to\": 5670}, {\"ngram\": \"a stately hotel\", \"from\": 5721, \"to\": 5736}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 5773, \"to\": 5782}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5786, \"to\": 5794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And once again, when it comes to dining, Lyon is a constant delight.\", \"from\": 5797, \"to\": 5865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5838, \"end\": 5842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0043492335802594e-40, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dining\", \"from\": 5830, \"to\": 5836}, {\"ngram\": \"a constant delight\", \"from\": 5846, \"to\": 5864}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given how sumptuous lunch can be - we also enjoyed a fabulous midday meal at the famous Brasserie des Brotteaux, which recently celebrated its 110th anniversary - it's customary to make suppertime a late affair.\", \"from\": 5866, \"to\": 6077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5968, \"end\": 5977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Brotteaux\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brotteaux\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Brotteaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Brotteaux\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how sumptuous lunch\", \"from\": 5872, \"to\": 5891}, {\"ngram\": \"a fabulous midday meal\", \"from\": 5917, \"to\": 5939}, {\"ngram\": \"its 110th anniversary\", \"from\": 6005, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"suppertime\", \"from\": 6052, \"to\": 6062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrons at Pimousse can watch chef Pierre-Michael Martin in the open kitchen preside over a wide variety of dishes.\", \"from\": 6079, \"to\": 6194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6129, \"end\": 6135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999994288484043, \"rank\": 5.686906873816925e-07, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Patrons\", \"from\": 6079, \"to\": 6086}, {\"ngram\": \"Pimousse\", \"from\": 6090, \"to\": 6098}, {\"ngram\": \"the open kitchen preside\", \"from\": 6139, \"to\": 6163}, {\"ngram\": \"a wide variety\", \"from\": 6169, \"to\": 6183}, {\"ngram\": \"dishes\", \"from\": 6187, \"to\": 6193}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For a first visit, put yourselves in his hands, and be surprised by the feast that lands, dish by dish, on your table.\", \"from\": 6195, \"to\": 6313, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a first visit\", \"from\": 6199, \"to\": 6212}, {\"ngram\": \"his hands\", \"from\": 6232, \"to\": 6241}, {\"ngram\": \"the feast\", \"from\": 6263, \"to\": 6272}, {\"ngram\": \"dish\", \"from\": 6293, \"to\": 6297}, {\"ngram\": \"your table\", \"from\": 6302, \"to\": 6312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, there is Tetedoie, designed and bearing the name of Michelin-starred chef Christian Tetedoie, once a pupil of the famous Paul Bocuse.\", \"from\": 6315, \"to\": 6457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6376, \"end\": 6392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michelin-starred\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}, {\"begin\": 6398, \"end\": 6407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999348314239643, \"rank\": 6.517282281839716e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"type